<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS - COMPONENT
        CHANGES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>COMPONENT CHANGES</title>
        <para>In order to achieve more precise valve timing, a new valve train assembly is used on engines effective
            with serial number 532981 (
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150502">5.2</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            ).
        </para>
        <para>These new components include:</para>
        <para>1 - Camshaft Assembly</para>
        <para>12 - Roller Tappet</para>
        <para>6 - Roller Tappet Guide</para>
        <para>12 - Push Rod</para>
        <para>12 - Rocker Arm Assembly</para>
        <para>12 - Valve Rotator</para>
        <para>12 - Valve Spring</para>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>DO NOT INTERMIX VALVE TRAIN COMPONENTS, CONSULT PARTS MANUAL FOR CORRECT SERVICE PART NUMBERS.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="ef4150502" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="cg12530" filename="../figcg1/CG12530.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 5.2 Valve Train Component Comparison.</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
